The holidays are not free everywhere.
In Hungary, free days are precisely defined by law, and it has already become common practice for working days to move around the holidays, which is less than what awaits us next year.
In the European Union and in America, the holidays are not uniform.
The Hungarian legal system distinguishes between national and state holidays and working days of rest.
The working days of peace are usually related to church holidays or to important historical events.
Here we also celebrate the New Year: the last day of the old and the first day of the new year is free to work - for the New Year already so that people can rest after Christmas.
