What kind of insurance is appropriate for me?
Insurance of a car that protects the driver in the event of an accident. represents a considerable expense, which depends on various factors such as age, condition, sex, length of holding of the driver's license, the type of vehicle to be insured or its use, etc.
Having a car is just the beginning.
Choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing a car model.
First of all, we need to clarify what we are talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between the insurance company and the insurer.
This obligation shall take the form of an insurance contract which provides that the insurance undertaking shall receive an agreed amount of insurance in a certain amount in order to take care of the payment of damages in the event of an insurance event.
Insurance is the price of insurance, which is determined with regard to various factors such as age, condition, sex, length of holding the driver's license, type of vehicle being insured or its use, etc.
Insurance companies set their prices on the basis of statistics, so the higher the probability of an accident, the higher the insurance rate.
For this reason, both people over the age of 25 and women have to pay lower insurance, as statistics show that they have a lower risk index due to their caution.
In the same way, on the basis of controls, insurance companies concluded that people living in a marriage have fewer accidents than free drivers.
The way the vehicle is used will affect the frequency of driving, and thus the probability that it will have some accident.
With the increase in the frequency of rides, the probability increases.
There are many variables that insurance companies consider when determining the price of insurance.
Therefore, the driver must study the situation well in order to choose the insurance that best matches his or her insurance profile.
Here we will show you the most important variables for choosing one type of insurance, which, in addition to being suitable for the type of insurance, will also be at a reasonable price.
People under the age of twenty-five are faced with various drawbacks such as little experience with driving and short-stay driving license when they want to negotiate insurance at an affordable price.
Although it is ideal for good coverage, insurance against all risks, there are also cheaper options.
The most careful drivers can choose insurance against all the risks with the reduction of the insurance so that they get insurance coverage of all the risks, but at a more affordable price.
This type of contract would presuppose the participation of the client in the remuneration of the insured event.
“The part of the insurance event that the client will provide will be determined in advance when determining the price of the insurance, which will be higher, although less it would be to participate,” explains Luis Noguera, chief executive officer of First Europe in Spain, an internet provider of insurance.
Another option is insurance extended to other participants of the operation so that the client is insured against damage caused to other persons, but not against damage to his own car.
In addition, it would be insured against theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
Recommendations.
If you are under the age of twenty-five, try to be careful and avoid accidents as much as possible, as this will affect your bonus and allow you to reduce the insured in the future.
The bonus is a reduction in the basic rate that the insurance company has.
In contrast, malus is an increase in the mentioned basic rate.
"Bonus and malus will depend on the insurance company and its profits.
If the insurance company has a good year, it will be able to afford to increase the bonus,” explains Noguera.
After exceeding the limit of twenty-five years, drivers have it easier when they go to get insurance, as the client’s risk index decreases, thanks to the acquired experience.
For this reason, it is most recommended to take out insurance against all the risks with a discount.
“Young people usually can’t take advantage of the experience gained in the moment of an accident, and even when driving,” assures the director of the European company in Spain, adding that most accidents occur in the second year of driving.
However, if the client is married but does not have children yet, it is better to arrange insurance against all the risks, if his economic situation allows.
Families with children are considered to be a clientele with the lowest risk index and therefore their premiums will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be insurance against all risks with an insurance discount (which could amount to 300 euros) or with a high bonus, insurance extended to other operators, starting the third year after the purchase of the vehicle.
“Their management is calmer and their purchasing power is higher, so they can afford the luxury of getting the highest discount,” Luis Noguera said.
Retirees are advised to take out insurance against all risks with a reduction of insurance (which amounts to 150 euros) or insurance extended to other operators if a high bonus has been achieved.
It must be said that car insurance is something important not only because it protects the driver in the event of an accident, but also because it represents a considerable expense, which is a good reason to properly study the insurance options that would suit us the most.
