The German Dax index grew by 2.6 percent and the French CAC40 increased by 2.3 percent.
Some time ago, market credit stress was shown to be in full force after the European Central Bank’s three-month cash package auctioned these funds to European commercial banks at a rate of 4,7 %, the highest since April 2001.
